e fuel for excellence. Rest, vacation or a payrise can't make you create excellence in your work. Findbwhat makes you passionate about what you do\n\n- Janna\n|\nIn a world where the larger majority of society is careless, it’s the small percentage of people who make the choice to be different and prioritize relationships that stand out.\n\n- Farshad Asl, The 'No Excuses' Mindset: A Life of Purpose, Passion, and Clarity\n|\nNo one should ever despair because the entrance to his or her chosen career path is clogged. There is an ancient saying: 'The persistent drip wears through stone.\n\n- Kentetsu Takamori, Something You Forgot...Along the Way: Stories of Wisdom and Learning\n|\nIf everything seems under control, you're not going fast enough.\n\n- Mario\n|\nIf you leave your dreams on your pillow, you might as well just stay in bed. To make dreams come true you’ve got to get up and take action.\n\n- Toni Sorenson, The Great Brain Cleanse\n|\nWe are all too often told by someone that we are too old, too young, too different, too much the same, and those comments can be devastating.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg, The Force of Kindness: Change Your Life with Love & Compassion\n|\nHappiness is, when it comes to the understanding of its meaning, to sometimes be unhappy.\n\n- Hasse\n|\nComfort zone: simply means the routine of one’s daily life – it is a psychological state in which one feels familiar, safe, at ease, and secure.\n\n- Roy\n|\nA sandwich and a cup of coffee, and then off to violin-land, where all is sweetness and delicacy and harmony.\n\n- Arthur Conan Doyle, The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes\n|\nInstead of blue skies and sunshine, there are grey clouds and endless rain that seeps into your bones, your soul.\n\n- Cathy Cassidy, Angel Cake\n|\nAvoidable human misery is more often caused not so much by stupidity as by ignorance, particularly our ignorance about ourselves.\n\n- Carl Sagan, The Demon-Haunted World: Science as a Candle in the Dark\n|\nO, how this spring of love resemblethThe uncertain glory of an April day,Which now shows all the beauty of the sun,And by and by a cloud takes all away!\n\n- William Shakespeare, The Two Gentlemen of Verona\n|\nThe greatest moments in our lives occur when we surrender: birth, love, and death.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nIntegrity is doing the right thing when nobody's watching, and doing as you say you would do.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nHealth, wealth, happiness,live long and always prosper,have families and also friends,let them be lasting in me forever.\n\n- Toba Beta, My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut\n|\nWorry about today, tomorrow will take care of itself.\n\n- Tapan Ghosh, Faceless The Only Way Out\n|\nYet, even amidst the hatred and carnage, life is still worth living. It is possible for wonderful encounters and beautiful things to exist.\n\n- Hayao\n|\nA flower blooming in the desert proves to the world that adversity, no matter how great, can be overcome.\n\n- Matshona\n|\n[Grief] is everything. It is the fabric of selfhood, and beautifully chaotic. It shares mathematical characteristics with many natural forms.\n\n- Max Porter, Grief is the Thing with Feathers\n|\nAnd so even though we face the difficulties of today and tomorrow, I still have a dream. It is a dream deeply rooted in the American dream.\n\n- Martin\n|\nIt's an enormous wall that's built between you and your dreams. And if every day, you just chip away... It may take ten years, but eventually you just might see some light.\n\n- Edward\n|\nEmbrace every new day with gratitude, hope and love.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nDo not be an average person, average is not normal, average is lazy. set goals, dream more, break the rules and become a better person you want be. BE HUMBLE AND KIND\n\n- Futty-fuze\n|\nYou do not have to be beautiful.You do not even have to be intelligent.All you have to do is practice kindness,for that is our purpose.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nIf life is a magnificent journey, then peace is the way and 